HEADWORD: Larvate
<hw>Lar"vate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>larva</ets>
mask.]</ety> <def>Masked; hence, concealed; obscure; -- applied in
medicine to doubtful cases of some diseases; <as>as, <ex>larvate</ex>
pneumonis; <ex>larvate</ex> epilepsy</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Larvated</ent>⟦br⟧
